C-states bug can cause CPUs to hang when C-states are enabled.  C-states enable CPUs to halt temporarily when they are not in active use, saving power.

The bug affects various Intel CPUs on various vendors' platforms.

To fix on Dell servers:

Reboot the server while on the ILOM console
Press F2 to enter the BIOS configuration menu 
Select Processor Settings 
Scroll down "C States" and "C1E"
Use the arrow keys to set both to Disabled 
Press ESC repeatedly and select "Save changes and exit"